Join us in developing the next generation of applications, tools, and infrastructure that will allow us to achieve our aggressive growth plans.ABOUT ACEABLEWe are a well funded, market leading startup in Austin, Texas who is helping people drive their lives forward by giving them access to the required education, vocational, and professional certification they need to move up in the world. Aceable uses a mobile-first platform that allows people to learn on the go no matter where they might be. Aceable's first products, Aceable Drivers Ed and Aceable Defensive Driving, are already leading the market in Texas and will soon be available nationwide. In only one year, we’ve captured a significant share of the Drivers Ed market with hundreds and thousands of users across Texas, California, Florida, Illinois, and Ohio. In the future, we’ll grow our impact even further by expanding to other states and launching new products in new markets.OUR ENGINEERING TEAM (YOUR NEW TEAMMATES)Our Engineering Team tackles complex operational and product problems as a team. They’re proven developers, both from their pre-Aceable careers and having created the “clean” code we use for our current platforms. At Aceable, you’ll have the opportunity to work closely with a tight-knit group and help the lay the framework for the expansion of our Engineering Department.
